      <p class="supporting-questions">Yes. It creates professional-looking curls and waves with less heat damage. Results last most of the day.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Is the Dyson Airwrap worth the price?</h3>
      <p class="supporting-questions">For regular stylists, yes. It replaces multiple tools and reduces salon visits. For occasional use, it's harder to justify.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What are alternatives to the Dyson Airwrap?</h3>
      <p class="supporting-questions">The Shark FlexStyle is the closest competitor at about half the price, with slightly less polished results.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How long do Airwrap curls last?</h3>
      <p class="supporting-questions">On average, curls last 8–12 hours. Using the cool shot setting and light hairspray extends hold time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Is the Dyson Airwrap worth it for everyday hair styling?</h3>
      <p class="supporting-questions">The Dyson Airwrap is worth it for anyone who styles their hair at least 4-5 times per week and wants to reduce heat damage. At $599, it replaces a hair dryer, curling iron, and smoothing brush. For occasional stylists, the Shark FlexStyle ($300) offers similar technology at lower cost.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What does Coanda effect mean in the Dyson Airwrap?</h3>
      <p class="supporting-questions">The Coanda effect is a fluid dynamics phenomenon where airflow attaches to a curved surface. In the Airwrap, high-velocity air from the barrel creates a vortex that draws hair toward it and wraps it around — no clamp required. This reduces direct heat contact and minimizes damage.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How long does it take to learn to use the Dyson Airwrap?</h3>
      <p class="supporting-questions">Most users need 3-5 sessions to achieve consistent results. The self-wrapping barrels require holding the hair section close to the barrel and letting the airflow do the work. Tutorials on YouTube speed up the learning curve significantly. After 2 weeks, most users describe it as intuitive.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can the Dyson Airwrap be used on all hair types?</h3>
      <p class="supporting-questions">The Dyson Airwrap works on fine, medium, and thick hair. Thin/fine hair responds best to the barrels for soft curls. Thick or coarse hair benefits most from the smoothing brushes for blowouts. Very tightly coiled hair types may find the barrels less effective than wand alternatives.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
